description: Deletes a subnet group. You cannot delete a default subnet group or one that is associated with any clusters.

parameters.name: SubnetGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the subnet group to delete.

nested_items.name: SubnetGroup
nested_items.description: The subnet group object that has been deleted.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the subnet group.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: A description of the subnet group.

nested_items.name: VpcId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Virtual Private Cloud identifier (VPC ID) of the subnet group.

nested_items.name: Subnets
nested_items.description: A list of subnets associated with the subnet group.

nested_items.name: Identifier
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the subnet.

nested_items.name: AvailabilityZone
nested_items.description: The Availability Zone where the subnet resides.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the Availability Zone.

nested_items.name: SupportedNetworkTypes
nested_items.description: The network types supported by this subnet. Returns an array of strings that can include --ipv4', --ipv6', or both, indicating whether the subnet supports IPv4 only, IPv6 only, or dual-stack deployments.

nested_items.name: ARN
nested_items.description: The ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the subnet group.

nested_items.name: SupportedNetworkTypes
nested_items.description: The network types supported by this subnet group. Returns an array of strings that can include --ipv4', --ipv6', or both, indicating the IP address types that can be used for clusters deployed in this subnet group.
